\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. nodiflora} (L.) Michx,{\i  Fl. Bor. Amer.}{\b  2}: 15 (1803). Perennial herb with procumbent, non-flowering stems rooting at the nodes, and ascending flowering stems 15-30 cm. Leaves 1-2·5 cm, obovate to oblanceolate, with a long-cuneate base, remotely serrate in the distal half. Flowers in short, stout axillary spikes 5-7 mm in diameter; peduncles much exceeding the subtending leaves. Calyx lobed almost to the base. Corolla 2 mm wide, sparsely pubescent without, white; lobes subequal.{\i  Wet, grassy places, usually near the sea. Mediterranean region.} Al Bl Co Cr Hs It ?Sa Si Tu.
\par

