\pard\f0\fs28 Monoecious herbs with opposite leaves. Flowers axillary. Perianth absent. Stamen 1. Ovary 4-locular, with 1 anatropous, pendent ovule in each loculus. Styles 2, filiform. Fruit separating into (2-)4 mericarps. Seeds with fleshy endosperm.
