\pard\f0\fs28 Submerged, amphibious or terrestrial herbs, with axillary glandular scales, and sometimes with peltate cauline hairs, otherwise glabrous. Leaves simple. Flowers solitary, or 1 male and 1 female flower in the same leaf-axil. Bracteoles 0 or 2 (in European species), membranous. Anthers reniform. Mericarps with rounded, keeled or winged margin.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    5 well-defined groups of species can be recognized in Europe, and hybridization between species of different groups is unknown. The amphibious species are very variable, and identification is made difficult because of the vegetative similarity of different species when growing in similar habitats.
